 10th century by the wife of the Holy Roman Emperor Otto the Great. She became regent after his death and was revered as a saint. The given name increased in popularity in England during the 19th century, when it was borne by the wife of King William IV; she was the daughter of the ruler of the German duchy of Saxe-Meiningen. The Australian city of Adelaide was named in her honour."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Adélaïde d’Arsac was born about 1210, in Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France, her father, Pierre III d’Arsac, was 31 and her mother, Talaise de Lamarque, was 31. She had at least 1 daughter with Bertrand « Trancaléon » de Lomagne. She died in Beaumont-de-Lomagne, Tarn-et-Garonne, Occitanie, France."},"et":{"about 1210–":"umbes 1210–Surnud","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1205–1270":"1205–1270","1227–1253":"1227–1253","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1180–1256":"1180–1256","before 1227":"enne 1227","1227":"1227","1205":"1205","1256":"1256","1210":"1210","1253":"1253","about 1210":"umbes 1210","1270":"1270","1180":"1180","Beaumont-de-Lomagne, Castelsarrasin, Tarn-et-Garonne, Occitanie, France":"Beaumont-de-Lomagne, Tarn-et-Garonne, Occitanie, Prantsusmaa","Beaumont-de-Lomagne,  Castelsarrasin, Tarn-et-Garonne, Occitanie, France":"Beaumont-de-Lomagne, Tarn-et-Garonne, Occitanie, Prantsusmaa","Arsac, Lesparre-Médoc,  Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1210–":"noin 1210–Kuollut","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1205–1270":"1205–1270","1227–1253":"1227–1253","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1180–1256":"1180–1256","before 1227":"ennen vuotta 1227","1227":"1227","1205":"1205","1256":"1256","1210":"1210","1253":"1253","about 1210":"noin 1210","1270":"1270","1180":"1180","Beaumont-de-Lomagne, Castelsarrasin, Tarn-et-Garonne, Occitanie, France":"Beaumont-de-Lomagne, Tarn-et-Garonne, Occitanie, Ranska","Beaumont-de-Lomagne,  Castelsarrasin, Tarn-et-Garonne, Occitanie, France":"Beaumont-de-L